It is the more to be regretted that Eppendorff did not read, or at least annotate, the letters more thoroughly: for not one in twenty has his comments. After the breach he continued for a time to write hostile animadversions on Erasmus ; but it appears that he soon lost interest in this. If there is any truth in the insinuation that he was in difficulties for money, he was doubtless glad enough to dispose of a book, the author of which he now detested‚ for some part of the gold orown which it had eost: and thus it was in the second-hand book market for Stibarus to buy a few years later.
